  "mythologyStories": {
    "intro": "When the gods killed her father Thiazi, Skadi armed herself and went to <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Asgard\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=asgard\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Asgard'\">Asgard</a> seeking compensation. The gods offered her a husband from among them, but she could only choose by looking at their feet. She chose what she thought were <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Baldr\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=baldur\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Baldr'\">Baldr</a>'s beautiful feet, but they belonged to <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Njord\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=njord\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Njord'\">Njord</a>. The marriage failed because Skadi could not bear the cries of seagulls at the shore, and <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Njord\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=njord\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Njord'\">Njord</a> could not sleep with the howling of wolves in the mountains. She is also associated with the binding and torture of <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Loki\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=loki\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Loki'\">Loki</a>, whom she helped bind with his son's entrails."
  },
